
*** Don't forget to change AM_INIT_AUTOMAKE([nngssrv], [1.1.1]) ***
*** then re-run autoconf to regenerate configure from configure.in ***


1.1.22 AvK 2007-02-24, 2009-05-20, 2009-08-30
- added more configuarable items:
  - idle_check_interval
  - ratings-intervals
  - max_idle
  - max_login_idle
  - rating_read_interval
  - ladder_sift_interval
  - conffile.default_komi19
  - conffile.default_komi13
  - conffile.default_komi9
- changed rdbm_open()s to use xyfilename() instead of hard-coded pathnames.
- idem xystat() for nratingsfile.
- fixed missing spaces in install-scripts for datafiles/directories.
- replaced all references to [v]snprintf() by my_[v]snprintf()
This was needed because the library-functions MAY return values >= dstlen.
- introduced automatic creation of admin-account
- removed various function-static buffers
- instead added utils.c/poolstr_dup() as a poor man's garbage collector.
- allow logfile to have the datetime at the beginning of the lines,
instead of at the end.
- refixed missing space in install-data shell scripts.

1.1.21 AvK 2007-02-21
- added default_komi and default_komi9 to configurable items.
- silly tell-command returned prematurely.
- Say/tell/shout/kibitz/channel/etc-Formatstrings. Sigh.
- Removed some more double-indexing of [pg]array.
- (GIFU2006) fixed bugs that were introduced (in 1.1.15??) 
by changing calloc() -->> malloc(); added some memset()...
- use server_http (instead of hardcoded nngs.cosmic.org) in last line
of usage-command.
- added handling of dotted quad in lists/ban file
- network.c : netstruct.in_full is never set to anything != zero.
plan to reuse it.
- moved more tunable constants to the conffile.
- added fromport (portnumber) into netstruct.
- changed return form xystat() to be st_size iff stat() returns >=0
- changed player_write() to only clear is_dirty if file was written
succesfully. (defined by newsize > oldsize/2, which seems fair enough).
This will result in NNGS to retry writing if previous writes were
unsuccessful (caused by disk-full conditions).
Previously, playerfiles could get truncated on disk-full conditions.

