1.1.19 AvK 2005-10-11
- removed unnecessary extern from function declarations in headers.
- renamed the ladder functions. They all start with ladder_ now.
- renamed globals in mink.c to mink_*
- Added support for chroot(). Set CHROOT_DIR to empty if you don't want it.
  - chroot/fork will probably only work on unix/linux platforms.
    windows people don't seem to need security, anyway.
  chroot() involves a lot of changes.
  - the tempfile-mechanism needs a /tmp/ subdirectory in jail.
  for safety: if chroot is wanted but impossible: nngssrv should fail.
  sending mail from the program needs to be changed for chroot():
  a direct client to a SMTP 'mta' needs to be set up. (the mail-binary needs
  access to the / or /usr filesystem anyway.
  - sending mail by SMTP needs gethostbyname(), which needs /etc/resolv.conf
  and/or/ /etc/hosts, which should be present in the jail, and need to
  be copied there. a working DNS will also be needed, if mail is
  realayed to any other MTA than "localhost"
  because mail can block (either way ...) a separate spooling mechanism
  plus a child-process are needed.
  - chroot/smtp will *probably not work on windows*.
- new files : conffile.[ch].
  All the pahnames/strings/configuration-items are now kept
  in a configfile (textfile) , which is read at startup.
  a Fixed filename 'nngs.cnf' is assumed (from current directory)
  , an alternate path/file can be specified by a '-c path/file' option
  on the commandline.
  If no conffile is found, a nngs.cnf IS WRITTEN in the
  current directory. This will contain the "compiled in" pathnames.
  This file is intended to serve as a template for further customisation.
  Note: not all combinations of pathnames are valid, but it will now be
  -at least- possible to put the data and binary into separate locations
  , and split the data into 'constant' files (eg helpfiles) and
  'variable' (players/games/results) parts.
  - started to put boolean variables into conffile (allow_unregistered)
- changed some of the configuration-items (filename-suffixes)
  to "non configurable", and dropped them from autoconf.
- changed LOG_FILE//log_file to contain the full pathname. Now you can put
  the logfile anywhere you want.
  The logfile.portnumber-feature has been removed. If you want it, you'll
  have to edit the conffile.
- idem for logons
- New files udp_command.[ch] An attempt at udp interface.
  This is intended for a PHP web interface on a "local" machine. Putting a
  "standard" client interface into PHP (including login/password: persistent
  sessions) was too hard for me.
  The protocol is basically "commandline over datagrams" which seems
  silly at first glance, but it works. Great tool for monitoring/debugging
  an active server, too.
  The udp-socket normally binds to 127.0.0.1 (localhost) port 9696/udp,
  this to avoid unnecessary vulnarabilities.
- Player-db rework. Sorting out the variables into "persistent" and
  "session-instanciated" variables (which *should* behave different on when
  swapping slots) Found some variables that where never even referenced or
  used :-] Moved fields into substructs && massive renaming.
- more renaming ... trying to get rid off 1-letter variables && double
- added some comment on ip_ban.c, which I am very fond of...
  indexing.

